criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult patients 18-65 years of age;

          -  previously untreated indolent nonfollicular non-Hodgkin's lymphoma;

          -  active disease;

          -  >=3 involved sites.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  typical chronic lymphocytic leukemia;

          -  other malignancies within 3 years before study, except basal or squamous cell skin
             cancer or cancer in situ of the cervix;

          -  systemic corticosteroid use for >1 month;

          -  significant cardiovascular disease;

          -  central nervous system involvement;

          -  hepatitis B or C virus infection, or HIV infection.
